&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intermediate Care Service - Somerset HUB Care Clinician Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term contract until March 2021 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to be a part of an exciting new service we are providing? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to work within the Somerset Hub Coordinating Care team for a fixed term period until March 2021 however there is the potential for this service to move into a permanent vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be an integral part of the Coordination team through the winter months in moving this service forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fast paced team which consists of Clinicians and Administrative staff, due to the current COVID climate and an extended Bed Coordination hub this offers new challenges and therefore we are looking for dynamic staff who love to be challenged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working within the Somerset Hub for Coordinating Care across both the Primary Link GP referral service, and the countywide Bed Coordination Team. As part of the Bed Coordination team you will be asked to work across the Somerset Acute Trusts to include Musgrove Park Hospital and Yeovil District Hospital therefore you must be able to drive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perhaps you are a qualified Nurse or Therapist looking for a rewarding and new challenge? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll have strong communication skills and will enjoy working within a fast paced environment with a supportive team around you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service hours are 08:00-21:30 7 days a week 365 days a year and will be worked in shift patterns, this includes bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
